**Egyptian Pyramids**

The Egyptian pyramids are some of the most famous and impressive structures from ancient Egypt. They were built as tombs for pharaohs, who were the kings of Egypt. The pyramids served as monumental burial sites and were designed to help the pharaohs in the afterlife.

**Example: The Great Pyramid of Giza**
One of the most well-known pyramids is the Great Pyramid of Giza, built for Pharaoh Khufu (also known as Cheops) around 2580-2560 BC. It is the largest of the three pyramids on the Giza plateau and was originally 146.6 meters (481 feet) tall. The Great Pyramid was one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World and is the only one that still exists today.
